==English==

===Etymology===
Originally referred to delaying the printing of a [[newspaper]] for late-breaking news.

===Interjection===
'''[[Stop]] [[the]] [[press]]es!'''

# {{idiom}} Used to introduce especially [[new]], [[important]], [[surprising]], or [[recent]] developments.

===Example===
* "Stop the presses!  I always wanted to say that.  Okay, start the presses!"  
* "That takes 4 hours!"

===See also===
*[[hold the phone]]
*[[stop press]]

